@smijolovic, a quick update.  We decided to revert this change after a conversation balancing the pros and cons.

While older versions of Podman did not make pull errors fatal when a local image was found, Podman's goal is to remain compatible with Docker.  `docker build --pull` however will always pull the image and error if it could not be pulled.

I opened https://github.com/containers/podman/pull/9144 but also corrected the --help message to match the behaviour.
